The paper deals with the problem of generating common randomness from correlated signals observed by multiple terminals, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of Renyi entropy, which is a concept commonly used in coding theory (cs.CC) and cryptography (cs.CR).
